The paper deals with face anonymization using a generative adversarial network, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.MM) sub-categories. The paper also discusses privacy and security concerns, which could be categorized under cryptography and security (cs.CR). The use of a conditional GAN and the generation of highly realistic faces could be considered as contributions to the field of deep learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
